=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: POP &amp; Wizards: Less need for TL &amp; TP?</span><hr size=1> Actually I like porting.. I let others set the price.. And if someone is broke or they are obviously a lowbie then I don't charge. Most times I don't ask for donations and sometimes people don't give any. Which I don't mind. I'm only a 40 wizard and sometimes I don't feel like soloing or finding a group just cuz I'm not in the mood to kill something. But I don't mind sitting in gfay or nexus porting and TL'ing people. I make money and meet kool people. And sometimes someone offers you 100pp or something cuz they are in a super rush or your help out a lowbie who has a 60 main wizard and gives you a golden bracer(true storie) <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> . I hope TP and TL don't come useless to us.<br> <p>Darrtev Olath'Vlos<BR>Wizard of Solusek Ro<BR> -Xev-</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/umagisterdarkshadowquester.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Magisterdark Shadowquester</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://users.ids.net/~orion_b/seal_icon.bmp" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(3/23/02 10:56:42 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=14598.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://users.ids.net/~orion_b/seal_icon.bmp WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: POP &amp; Wizards: Less need for TL &amp; TP?</span><hr size=1> Ok. T&amp;D have give two sides to this PRO &amp; CON. Both are reasonable answers.<br><br>Now lets look at one aspect of Wizard Transport:<br><br>Entry to the Plains.<br><br>Wizards have a lock on this &amp; thus MUST be considered for any Plains Raids. No Wizard = No Epic.<br><br>If POP breaks the lock on Plains entry then what? Will it be a case of &quot;Wizards? Who needs them? We can bring all the Tanks &amp; Clerics we need at no cost!&quot;?<br><br>Remember again that I mean no insult to anyone,<br><br>Mags <p>37 Teir'Dal Necromancer, Solusek Ro.I want to go everywhere & Do everything & LIVE to do it again, but I wonder, still I wonder, are Gnomes Light meat or Dark?</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=passionfyre>Passionfyre</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(3/23/02 10:58:21 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=14598.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: POP &amp; Wizards: Less need for TL &amp; TP?</span><hr size=1> I allways port for CR's personally, they are just a pain in the butt.<br><br><br>True story, this happened to me today. I ported someone to DL for the Nexus Scion. they hail the Scion. then accidentally attack the scion. They go SPLAT. so, I gate to GD where they were bound and TP'd them back. LOL it was funny from my perspective, and I can just imagine the guy at home going &quot;The Nexus Scion hits me for...oh sh*t...&quot; <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  the fastest CR for him ever he said *G* It makes me feel good to be able to help people like that.<br><br>I think that TP's are a beneficial, and oft times profitable, addition to the wizard class, like Rezz for clerics, crack for chanters and SoW for treehuggers. /shrug<br><br>if we get our ports made less usefull by this expansion the worst it can do is nerf a suplemental source of income for my wizard. and thats the worse I see it doing. I will still be able to gate all over the world, alter planes hate and sky, and TL to bind spot. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/umagisterdarkshadowquester.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Magisterdark Shadowquester</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://users.ids.net/~orion_b/seal_icon.bmp" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(3/23/02 11:01:56 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=14598.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://users.ids.net/~orion_b/seal_icon.bmp WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: POP &amp; Wizards: Less need for TL &amp; TP?</span><hr size=1> And, ofcourse, Summon Corpse for my Class.<br><br>However, ANY Necromancer will tell you that making a living by offering SC as other than a side line service is a fast way to go broke.<br><br>Mags <p>37 Teir'Dal Necromancer, Solusek Ro.I want to go everywhere & Do everything & LIVE to do it again, but I wonder, still I wonder, are Gnomes Light meat or Dark?</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=eaminwhitefalcon>Eamin Whitefalcon</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer<BR>¡Viva la inquisición!</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(3/23/02 11:08:31 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=14598.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://web.tampabay.rr.com/eqsite/Eamin_small.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=tit